    "privacyPolicyPart1": "<h1>Privacy Policy</h1><p class=\"stand\">Last updated: August 19, 2025</p><section id=\"controller\"><h2>1. Name and Address of the Controller</h2><i>The controller responsible for data processing within the meaning of the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) is:</i>",
    "privacyPolicyPart2": "Responsible contact for website's contents:",
    "privacyProtectionOfficer": "Local Data Protection Officer",
    "privacyPolicyPart3": "<section id=\"purposes-legal-bases\"><h2>3. Purposes and Legal Bases of Processing</h2><ul><li><strong>Provision of the website and IT security</strong> (including server log files, error and security logs) pursuant to Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest in a secure, functional website).</li><li><strong>User login and access control via Keycloak</strong> pursuant to Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR (performance of the user contract) and Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (operation of a secure authentication and authorization system). Where the processing serves the performance of a task carried out in the public interest, it is additionally based on Art. 6(1)(e) GDPR in conjunction with the relevant statutory provision.</li></ul></section><section id=\"keycloak\"><h2>4. Authentication with Keycloak</h2><p>We use <strong>Keycloak</strong> as our identity and access management system (IdP). <strong>Passwords are never visible to us in plain text</strong>. Password processing takes place exclusively in the authentication service; we only receive information on whether a login was successful as well as a session/access token.</p><p>As part of login and session management, the following data may be processed, among others:</p><ul><li>User identifier (e.g., username, UID), roles/groups</li><li>Login/logout timestamps, status (success/failure)</li><li>Session/token IDs and validity periods</li><li>Technical metadata: IP address, date/time, user agent</li></ul><p>For the session, Keycloak sets technically necessary cookies (e.g., <code>KEYCLOAK_IDENTITY</code>, <code>KEYCLOAK_SESSION</code>, <code>AUTH_SESSION_ID</code>). These are required for login.</p></section><section id=\"login-logging\"><h2>5. Logging of Login Events</h2><p>For IT security, abuse prevention, and traceability of administrative actions, <strong>login events</strong> are logged. In particular, the following are recorded: timestamp, user ID, success/failure, IP address, and user agent. The legal basis is Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR.</p></section><section id=\"server-logs\"><h2>6. Server Log Files</h2><p>When our pages are accessed, the server automatically collects the following data: IP address, date and time of the request, time zone difference to GMT, requested URL/file, access status/HTTP status code, amount of data transferred, referrer, browser including version, operating system.</p></section><section id=\"cookies\"><h2>7. Cookies</h2><p>We only use <strong>technically necessary cookies</strong> for authentication and session management (Keycloak). <strong>No analytics, tracking, or marketing cookies</strong> are used.</p></section><section id=\"recipients\"><h2>8. Recipients and Processing on Behalf</h2><p>Internally, only authorized administrators have access to the data required for the respective purpose.</p></section><section id=\"obligation\"><h2>9. Obligation to Provide Data</h2><p>The provision of login data is required for the use of protected areas. Without this data, login and therefore the use of certain functions is not possible.</p></section><section id=\"rights\"><h2>10. Your Rights</h2><p>Under the GDPR, you in particular have the following rights: access (Art. 15), rectification (Art. 16), erasure (Art. 17), restriction of processing (Art. 18), data portability (Art. 20), as well as objection to processing based on Art. 6(1)(e) or (f) (Art. 21). Where processing is based on consent, you may withdraw your consent at any time with effect for the future (Art. 7(3)).</p><p>You also have the right to lodge a complaint with a data protection supervisory authority, in particular in the Member State of your residence, place of work, or place of the alleged infringement (Art. 77 GDPR).</p></section><section id=\"security\"><h2>11. Security</h2><p>We take technical and organizational measures pursuant to Art. 32 GDPR (e.g., TLS encryption, role-based access control, logging, and system hardening) to protect your data against loss, misuse, and unauthorized access.</p></section><section id=\"changes\"><h2>12. Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2><p>We update this privacy policy if functions, legal requirements, or organizational processes change. The current version can be accessed here.</p></section><section id=\"contact\"><h2>13. Contact</h2><p>If you have questions regarding the processing of your personal data, please contact the controller mentioned above or the data protection officer.</p></section>",
    "serviceProvider": "Service Provider",
